{
  "texts": [
    "AI technology can pre-analyze the selection of superlubricity materials, structural design, and operational principles, thereby accelerating the progress of related research.",
    "Tribological behavior analysis based on standard experimentsThe tribological standard test refers to the test conducted based on product-based and standardized friction and wear testing machines and referring to standardized processes [86][87][88][89][90].",
    "In fact, this part is the main source of data for friction informatics, which has repeatability and accumulation, and is often used to analyze the universal laws of tribological behavior [91-94].",
    "The tribological behavior includes the following aspects: (1) the processing of surface texture and its influence on wear resistance [95-99]; (2) wear image analysis and wear state recognition [100-107];(3) the correlation between tribological derived signals (such as acoustics, vibration, acoustic emission, and thermodynamics) and the state of friction and wear [108][109][110]; (4) the influence of the preparation process of friction pair materials on friction and wear behavior [111][112][113][114][115][116][117]; and (5) the influence of input conditions on friction and wear performance of tribological systems [118][119][120][121][122].",
    "Overall, it mainly includes three aspects: the relationship between state variables during the operation of tribological systems [123][124][125]; the evolution law of the tribological system behavior [126][127][128][129][130]; and the correlation law between the friction and wear performance and the system input and intrinsic variables [131][132][133][134]."
  ]
}